Don’t let a few stories scare you off, but just remember that you’re a visitor. Treat the forest with respect, be safe, and trust your gut if your intuition is telling you to leave.

In the spring, I was taking a walk in the woods when I had a feeling that I wasn’t supposed to be there. The air was heavy. There was no other sign of life like birds or anything. It had also gotten darker even though the sun wasn’t supposed to set for hours. So I went back home.

It’s not necessarily malevolent or anything unless you push your luck. I also feel like this happens in a lot of places, but particularly natural places like forests. Sometimes it’s just like a warning type of feeling.

The Appalachia stories on TikTok are funny bc most of it are campfire tales but if you’re from here and you get an uneasy feeling in the woods, you leave. You grow up understanding that you’re just a visitor and there’s ancient energy here that’s beyond comprehension.
